onsible or how it could happen.  I won't blame the CIA or the FBI for failing to protect the lives of so many.  I won't immediately jump to the conclusion that Osama Bin Laden or some other fundamental zionist Islamic group is responsible.<br><br>All I know is that several thousand Americans were brutally murdered today.  I would be surprised if between us all, that we don't know at least a few of these lost lives.  We can call it terrorism, or proponents can call it a justified attack, you are free to call it whatever you like.  <br><br>All I can do is hope for justice.  For one day at least, all of us that call ourselves Americans are simply that: Americans.  We are not simply Republicans and Democrats, liberals or conservatives.  We are more than European, African, Hispanic, Asian, Jew &amp; Arab.  If nothing else perhaps this attack will bring us together, if only for a little while.<br><br>Every fiber of my being screams for vengeance.  I'm afraid that these attacks are only the acts of terrorism.  We may never see these people punished.  If only we could know that this was sponsored by some organized government, our target would be clear, and retaliation swift.  Perhaps I am a fool to hope that some nation would actually sponsor an attack on civilians.  Whatever the case may be, I am one American who is prepared to fight for the lives of those who have been lost.<br><br>Some of you may disagree with the eye for an eye philosophy.  I don't claim that the indiscriminate destruction of civilians is the answer, but in war, as these people have just proven, innocents lives are lost.  I didn't post this to start an argument, I only express my thoughts as they come to me, angry though they may be.  I am not a praying man.  In fact, I have no belief in a supreme being.  For me, justice does not come in the afterlife, but only in the here and now. <br><br>Whatever you believe, whatever your feelings, whatever your national origins may be,  I hope at least that we can agree that this is, in fact, a tragedy.<br><br>I thank you for listening, and I thank the United States of America for granting me the freedom to think as I do, and to be able to put these thoughts in writing.<br><br>Arctic Icestorm<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umuzaak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Muzaak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/11/01 11:16:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=148.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I am in shock.</span><hr size=1> Arctic, I can say that your remarks are some of the most intelligible that I have read concerning today's attack on the USA. I agree with your sentiments. I, too, wish we could easily finger the perpetrators of this cowardly act of war. It would be easy to then take revenge with the hope justice is served.<br><br>Unfortunately, it will not be easy to reveal just who exactly are deserving a slow painful death for this crime against the citizens of the world. Yes, a crime against the world, since if it can so easily happen here in the United States it can also happen in London, Paris, Moscow... name the city. We all should have an interest in stopping such aggression.<br><br>I just hope the US goverment (especially GW Bush) grow some big brass ones and work tirelessly to bring the masterminds of this crime to justice. If justice is served in the courts or at the end of a pistol I care less. I just want it revealed who exactly is responsible and action taken against them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.